28/03/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH Deputy Security Minister Dragan Mektic announced on Sunday (27 March) that the BiH Ministries of Security and Justice are drafting a trilateral agreement on extradition of war crimes suspects among BiH, Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro. 
The document would be adopted at one of the next BiH Council of Ministers sessions and sent to Zagreb and Belgrade. 
The initiative was launched at the urging of High Representative Paddy Ashdown.
In other news, Republika Srpska (RS) Interior Minister Darko Matijasevic repeated Sunday that the government does not know the whereabouts of top RS indictee Radovan Karadzic. 
Matijasevic confirmed that the ministry is in touch with Karadzic's family, as well as friends and relatives of former Bosnian Serb military commander Ratko Mladic.
On Monday, US diplomat Lawrence Butler formally assumes the post of principal deputy high representative in BiH. 
Butler has been serving as US ambassador to Macedonia and had previous postings in Sofia and Belgrade. 
(Nezavisne novine -28/03/05; RTRS, NTV Hayat, Fena, PBS BiH, Pincom.info - 27/03/05)
